      {
        "time": 1773242912783,
        "link": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7437506371471732736?commentUrn=urn%3Ali%3Acomment%3A%28activity%3A7437506371471732736%2C7437519842053894145%29&dashCommentUrn=urn%3Ali%3Afsd_comment%3A%287437519842053894145%2Curn%3Ali%3Aactivity%3A7437506371471732736%29",
        "text": "Interesting take. The trust transfer from host to brand is definitely what makes podcast advertising powerful. When the audience already trusts the host, the recommendation feels much closer to word-of-mouth than traditional advertising.\n \nThe compounding effect is also underrated. Unlike most paid channels, those episodes continue to live and drive discovery long after the campaign ends.",
